==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portague
<hw>Por"ta*gue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Portuguese</er>.]</ety> <def>A Portuguese gold coin formerly
current, and variously estimated to be worth from three and one half to
four and one half pounds sterling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>portegue</asp> and
<asp>portigue</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ten thousand <qex>portagues</qex>, besides great pearls.</q>
<rj><qau>Marlowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portal</ent>⟦br⟧
